(42, 17, 15, 19, 103, 1, 4, 'glorified God', 'Healing and Gratitude Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing and gratitude. In Luke 17:15, the healed man glorifies God, while Psalms 103:1-4 emphasizes blessing the Lord for His healing benefits.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 15, 42, 17, 17, 18, 'glorified God', 'Gratitude and Glory to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of returning to glorify God after receiving healing. The SOURCE verse shows one leper glorifying God, while the TARGET passage emphasizes that only this leper returned to give glory, contrasting with the others who did not.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 15, 23, 38, 19, 22, 'glorified God', 'Praise and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of praising God following healing. In Luke, the healed man glorifies God, while in Isaiah, the living are called to praise the Lord for His salvation.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 15, 43, 9, 38, 38, 'glorified God', 'Expressions of Gratitude and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorifying God and expressing faith in response to healing. Both passages depict individuals who, upon recognizing their healing, respond with worship and acknowledgment of God''s power.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 15, 14, 32, 24, 26, 'glorified God', 'Gratitude and Humility in Healing', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to healing. In Luke, the healed man glorifies God, while Hezekiah initially fails to render thanks, leading to pride. Both passages emphasize the importance of humility and gratitude after receiving divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 15, 40, 9, 8, 8, 'glorified God', 'Glorifying God in Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to miraculous healings. In Luke, the healed individual returns to glorify God, while in Matthew, the multitudes marvel and glorify God for the power given to men.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 16, 44, 8, 5, 25, 'and he was a Samaritan', 'Samaritan Faith and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Samaritans in receiving healing and faith. In Luke, a Samaritan expresses gratitude, while in Acts, the Samaritans collectively respond to Philip''s preaching with belief and healing.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 16, 40, 10, 5, 5, 'Samaritan', 'Samaritans in Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Samaritans in Jesus'' ministry. In Luke, a Samaritan expresses gratitude, while Matthew instructs to avoid Samaritan cities, highlighting the complex relationship between Jesus and Samaritans.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
