(42, 17, 16, 42, 10, 32, 35, 'giving him thanks: and he was a Samaritan', 'Samaritan''s Compassion and Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize the Samaritan''s role in showing compassion and gratitude. In Luke 17:16, the Samaritan expresses thanks, while in Luke 10:32-35, he demonstrates compassion by caring for the wounded man.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 16, 66, 19, 4, 5, 'fell down on his face', 'Worship and Gratitude Connection', 'This connection highlights the act of falling down in worship and gratitude. Both passages depict individuals or beings expressing reverence and thanks, emphasizing the importance of worship in response to divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 16, 42, 9, 52, 56, 'Samaritan', 'Samaritan Reception and Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the Samaritan''s role in relation to Jesus. In Luke 17:16, a Samaritan expresses gratitude, while in Luke 9:52-56, Samaritans reject Jesus, highlighting contrasting responses to him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 16, 43, 4, 9, 9, 'Samaritan', 'Samaritan Recognition and Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Samaritans and their interactions with Jews. The Samaritan in Luke expresses gratitude, while the woman in John highlights the social divide between Jews and Samaritans.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 17, 19, 106, 13, 13, NULL, 'Gratitude and Forgetfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of ingratitude. In Luke 17:17, Jesus notes the absence of gratitude from the nine cleansed lepers, while Psalms 106:13 describes how the people forgot God''s works, indicating a lack of remembrance and appreciation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
